# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

We currently provide security attention to the most recent public release of JewelsStore Chat Widget and to actively maintained development work.

| Version | Supported |
| ------- | --------- |
| Latest public release | Yes |
| Older releases | No |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you discover a security issue related to JewelsStore Chat Widget, please do not publish it publicly before contacting us.

Please report security concerns privately through:

- Website: https://jewelsstore.shop
- Premium solutions: https://jewelsstore.shop/plugins
- English premium page: https://jewelsstore.shop/en/plugins

When reporting a vulnerability, please include:

- a clear description of the issue
- affected plugin version
- steps to reproduce
- screenshots or logs if relevant
- whether the issue affects the free version, premium version, or related licensing components

## Security Principles

JewelsStore Chat Widget is developed with attention to:

- controlled premium licensing workflows
- signed server response verification
- role-aware access to sensitive internal context
- summary-only internal context exposure where configured
- masking of sensitive information where applicable
- controlled connector and assistant access rules

## Responsible Disclosure

We ask researchers and users to practice responsible disclosure and allow time for review and remediation before public disclosure.
